"07/31/13 On tap at Rattle n Hum, NYC. Nitro being the blessing that it is, this one has set a high standard to live up to with it's handsome looks. First taste is of well managed malt. Listed in the ESB category it comes up shy on the hop side...not that that is a bad thing, IMO. Amusing lacing looks like it's done by a fledgling interior decorator or some Japanese painting of Sea Foam. All in all this is a distinctive beer that minds it's P's-&-Q's. In a word smooth."
